colorize_cell_library(25.10)                      colorize_cell_library(25.10)

Name
       colorize_cell_library - Colors each standard cell in the library, using
       the pre-color method

Syntax
       colorize_cell_library

       [-help]

       [-cell <cell_name>]

       [ [-reset ] | [-enforce ] ]

       Colors each standard cell in the library, using the pre-color method.

Parameters
       -cell <cell_name>
              Specifies   the   name   of  the  cell  to  colorize.  The  col-
              orize_cell_library command only targets the specified cell,  ir-
              respective of the cell type.

              Data_type: (libCell/ptnCell)+, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each colorize_cell_library parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man colorize_cell_library.

       -enforce
              Specifies that re-colorization will be enforced. It  colors  the
              cell even if it is already colored.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reset Resets the library cell color data. It cleans the color of every
              standard cell, except the LEF-color.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The following command resets the library cell color data.

                colorize_cell_library -reset

Related Information
              * setNanoRouteMode

              * Using the NanoRoute Router chapter in the Innovus User Guide

